<p>To see what the future and past have in common, take their average:</p>

<p><img src=3D"https://betterexplained.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-latexrende=
r/pictures/2ebca6dd13e2517240cb5517dd8b6092.png" width=3D"360" height=3D"39=
" alt=3D"\displaystyle{f_\text{even}(x) =3D \text{avg}[\text{future} + \tex=
t{past}] =3D \frac{f(x) + f(-x)}{2}}" class=3D"tex"></p>

<p>To see how the future and past differ, average their gap:</p>

<p><img src=3D"https://betterexplained.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-latexrende=
r/pictures/0162fe3f75aa6f77901cde5035475042.png" width=3D"356" height=3D"39=
" alt=3D"\displaystyle{f_\text{odd}(x) =3D \text{avg}[\text{future} - \text=
{past}] =3D \frac{f(x) - f(-x)}{2}}" class=3D"tex"></p>

