auto"><div><p>By the way, there is a use for ln(cosh) and its parabolic-to-=
linear behavior, for an object falling near the Earth's surface (gravity g)=
 with air drag proportional to speed-squared (drag force =3D b v^2, where b=
 is a constant in kg per meter). The solution to Newton's 2nd law: m d2y/dt=
2 =3D m g - b(dy/dt)^2, is y(t) =3D vt^2/g ln[cosh(g t/vt)), where y(t) is =
